# 🏠 HouseHaunt Backend (Flask)

A scalable backend system for a real estate platform, built with Flask.  
Handles authentication, property listings, transactions, and user workflows.

---

## 🚀 Features

- JWT Authentication & Authorization
- Role-Based Access Control (Admin, Agent, User)
- Property listing and management system
- Transaction and wallet logic
- KYC verification system
- Notifications system
- File upload & static asset handling
- Review and favorites system

---

## 🛠 Tech Stack

- Python (Flask)
- MongoDB
- PostgreSQL (basic)
- JWT Authentication
- Docker
- Nginx
- Render (deployment)

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```
/app
  /routes
  /models
  /services
  /utils
run.py
config.py
```

---

## ⚙️ Setup Instructions

### 1. Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/petercokey/house_haunt_flask.git
cd house_haunt_flask
```

### 2. Create virtual environment
```bash
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate   # Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
```

### 3. Install dependencies
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 4. Set environment variables
Create a `.env` file and add:
```
SECRET_KEY=your_secret_key
MONGO_URI=your_mongo_uri
JWT_SECRET_KEY=your_jwt_secret
```

### 5. Run the app
```bash
python run.py
```

---

## 🔐 API Overview

| Endpoint | Description |
|--------|------------|
| /auth/register | Register user |
| /auth/login | Login user |
| /properties | Manage listings |
| /transactions | Handle transactions |
| /users | User management |

